# LoadZone Core

- LoadZone is a monorepo for amateur football wellness monitoring with two main apps:
  `apps/app` for staff/admin and `apps/player` for player check-ins.
- Reuse existing packages before adding code:
  `@repo/design-system`, `@repo/database`, `@repo/auth`, `@repo/ai`.
- Keep changes minimal and focused. Do not add docs or tests unless the user asks.
- Use strict TypeScript with explicit parameter and return types. Avoid `any`.
- Prefer `@repo/*` imports for shared packages and `@/` for local app imports.
- Check whether a shared UI primitive already exists in `packages/design-system/components/ui`
  before creating a new component.
- Do not run builds by default. In Next.js work, only run build/dev commands if the user asks.
- Key domain entities: `Team`, `Season`, `Player`, `DailyEntry`, `PlayerDailyStats`,
  and `PushSubscription`.
- Never expose or log player tokens. Treat public player flows as security-sensitive.
